description:
In celebration of the Army’s 250th Birthday, the largest U.S. military parade in decades is scheduled for Flag Day – also President Trump’s 79th birthday. The event is expected to feature 150 vehicles including Paladins, M1A2 Abrams Tanks and Strykers and 50 aircrafts including Chinooks, Blackhawks and Apaches. 

WSJ breaks down what to expect at Trump’s military parade in Washington D.C.

author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Secretary of Education Linda McMahon is leading the administration’s fight against elite universities, including Harvard and Columbia. McMahon and President Trump have cut billions in government funding and demanded federal oversight on campuses. She sat down with WSJ to discuss her thinking and if there is room for compromise.
